<h2 id="orgcde36e9">Thoughts on Full Tuition</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgcde36e9">
<p>
As Manfred said, changing this is a cost to us: in application competitiveness and presumably research dollars available.
</p>

<p>
Of course, we're happy to do our part for the department, but it would be good to more about the basic situation and the expected benefits of this cost.
</p>

<p>
How big is the department deficit? How much has it changed recently? How does it compare to other
departments?  How much of this is due to the accounting model ?
</p>

<p>
What is going to happen to the extra tuition being charged? What fraction would go to the
Department/College/University? How much would be made available to us? Would it be discretionary spending? etc.
</p>

<p>
Historically, why was the requested amount 55%? Do we think jumping from 55% straight to 100% is really the right move, especially in the current funding environment? 
</p>
</div>
